==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leman
<hw>Le"man</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧"m⟦ait⟧n ⟦or⟧ l⟦ecr⟧m"⟦ait⟧n; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>lemman</ets>, <ets>lefman</ets>; AS.
<ets>le⟦oacute⟧f</ets> dear + <ets>mann</ets> man. See <er>Lief</er>,
and <er>Man</er>.]</ety> <def>A sweetheart, of either sex; a gallant, or
a mistress; -- usually in a bad sense.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au> <au>Spenser.</au> <au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lemanderin</ent>⟦br⟧
